{
  "body": "From https://docs.perl6.org/type/IO::Handle:\r\n\r\n> Note: unlike some other languages, Perl 6 does not use reference counting, and so **the file handles are NOT flushed or closed when they go out of scope nor reliably at program exit**. \r\n\r\nBut we do close file handles on program exit. See [RT #132030](https://rt.perl.org/Ticket/Display.html?id=132030).\r\n\r\nKeep this note but note that it is pre-2017.09 behavior.",
